  "prompt": "What is the nearest airport to Daytona Beach, and how do this cities tourist attractions compare to Birmingham's?",
  "response": "The nearest airport to Daytona Beach is Daytona Beach International Airport (DAB), located within the city limits. However, many travelers also use Orlando Sanford International Airport (SFB) or Orlando International Airport (MCO), which are both within about an hour's drive.\n\nComparing tourist attractions between Daytona Beach and Birmingham:\n\nDaytona Beach attractions:\n- Famous beaches\n- Daytona International Speedway\n- Daytona Beach Boardwalk and Pier\n- Beach racing heritage\n- Water sports and activities\n- NASCAR-related attractions\n\nBirmingham attractions:\n- Civil Rights historical sites\n- Birmingham Museum of Art\n- Birmingham Civil Rights Institute\n- Vulcan Park and Museum\n- Space and Rocket Center (nearby in Huntsville)\n- More urban and cultural focus\n\nDaytona Beach is more beach and motorsports-oriented, while Birmingham offers more historical and cultural attractions. The cities have quite different tourism profiles, with Daytona Beach being a beach destination and Birmingham being more of a historical and cultural center.",
